FBIS4-63742 "drsov101_b_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Bank Official Opposed to U.S.-Style Federal Reserve Bank Official Opposed to U.S.-Style Federal Reserve LD2405153894 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 1400 GMT 24 May 94 LD2405153894 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] Addressing a conference entitled "New Aspects of Reforming Russian Economy" in Moscow, Aleksandr Khandruyev, deputy chairman of the [Russian] Central Bank, vehemently opposed the transformation of the Russian Central Bank into a U.S.-style federal reserve system. Such a system cannot be imposed on to Russian realities in its existing form, and neither can any other model, he stressed.
